  <Method>
    <Step type="STEP" image="Red%20Beans%20and%20Rice_20250822_161200.jpg">Make &lt;a href='/GetRecipe?recipeName=Roux'&gt;Roux&lt;/a&gt;</Step>
    <Step type="STEP" image="Red%20Beans%20and%20Rice_20250822_161942.jpg">Add chicken stock to roux, bring to a simmer, stirring to combine.</Step>
    <Step type="STEP" image="Red%20Beans%20and%20Rice_20250822_161037.jpg">Saute sausage in a skillet until edges begin to brown.</Step>
    <Step type="STEP" image="Red%20Beans%20and%20Rice_20250822_161556.jpg">Add onion, celery and pepper to sausage.</Step>
    <Step type="STEP" image="Red%20Beans%20and%20Rice_20250822_161939.jpg">Continue cooking until vegetables have softened.</Step>
    <Step type="STEP" image="Red%20Beans%20and%20Rice_20250822_162011.jpg">Add red beans.</Step>
    <Step type="STEP" image="Red%20Beans%20and%20Rice_20250822_162044.jpg">Add chicken stock mixture, garlic, and half of the parsley.</Step>
    <Step type="STEP" image="Red%20Beans%20and%20Rice_20250822_162220.jpg">Add cajun seasoning, red pepper flakes, garlic powder, onion powder, pepper and salt.</Step>
    <Step type="STEP" image="Red%20Beans%20and%20Rice_20250822_162437.jpg">Stir to combine, bring to a boil, reduce to a simmer and cook for 20 minutes</Step>
    <Step type="STEP" image="">Stir in half of the remaining parsley.</Step>
    <Step type="STEP" image="Red%20Beans%20and%20Rice_20250822_163853.jpg">To serve, ladle into a bowl, Add a scoop of rice, top with a pinch of parsley.</Step>
  </Method>
